    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Dorothée Berryman"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>A passionate lover of jazz and French chanson, Dorothée Berryman offers an evening filled with tenderness, elegance, and emotion.<br><br>\n\nWith her warm voice and nuanced interpretation, she blends love and humor as she revisits treasures from the repertoire, notably by George Gershwin, Cole Porter, Jacques Prévert, and Joseph Kosma, not to mention the unique world of Colette Renard.<br><br>\n\nAn intimate evening where jazz meets poetry, brought to life by an artist who has always celebrated the timeless classics.<br>\nAn evening not to be missed for lovers of music, beautiful voices, and timeless classics!<br><br>\n\nFeaturing Vincent Réhel on piano, Dave Watts on double bass, and Camil Bélisle on drums.</p>\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){\niframe{width:100%;}\n}\n\n</style>"
      }
    ],
