    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "ROXANE BRUNEAU"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Extend the summer festivities right in the heart of the bustling Latin Quarter. HORS PROGRAMME is the event that will kick off your fall cultural season with a bang.<br><br>\n\nWith over 195,000 albums sold and 150 million streams, Roxane Bruneau is making great strides—and doing so with authenticity—on the Quebec music scene. <i>Dysphorie</i> (certified GOLD and winner of 1 Félix Award) and <i>Acrophobie</i> (certified GOLD and winner of 4 Félix Awards) cement her status as a popular idol. In 2023, she released <i>Submergé</i>, which became a top-selling album, won the Félix Award for Album of the Year—Pop in 2024, and was nominated in the prestigious Album of the Year category at the 2025 Junos. She stands out for her exceptional versatility, excelling equally in comedy, music, hosting, acting, and directing.</p>"
      }
    ],
